I made this map at the end of 2016 and never released it here.

This is a small speedrun map i made

FIXED AS CERTAIN PART DIDN'T WORK AS INTENDED ON CSS, PLEASE DISREGARD THE ORIGINAL bhop_rainbowroad BSP - and use this one instead.

My longest bhop map yet, It may seem random if you have never played Mario Kart but the design is obviously inspired by the 'Rainbow Road' track from that game, I have wanted to make a map inspired by that track for so long so I decided to do it, obviously I couldn't copy the same track so I just put my own twist on it. This map is pretty different not only from all my other maps but from most bhop maps in general, the gameplay is basically based around avoiding obstacles and gaining as much speed as possible in order to pull off the many skips in this map. Any bhopper of any skill level can beat this, but to be able to pull off every skip will take some patience and quite some time spent routing (at least for me it did) Map is designed to be fun to be played both fast and slow (but ideally fast since its rather largely scaled) If you choose to not do the fast route you will probably find you'll be losing speed quite frequently, I designed this map specifically to reward players for being fast and smooth. As I said there's several skips in this map, some of which are a lot harder than others.  Also has a little bonus I made quickly because I burned myself out making the main map and was really tired with this project by the end. This was just me experimenting and making something I thought would be fun so don't take it too seriously.

It isn't perfect, but I'm happy with it.

P.S - Music might get annoying if you plan on running this map for a long time

A map i started working on about 4-5 days ago, basically made the entire thing then did some play testing with a couple friends before i added triggers/playerclips to see what they thought, they liked the game play so i added some triggers, clips and improvements based on feedback. As well as some small detailing, was mostly square shaped rooms to begin with. 

Then Nairda was nice enough to let me playtest the map on the Ultima WL server, so a huge thanks to him and everyone who play tested it with me and gave feedback.

I aimed for this map to be a bit longer than the maps i usually make, kind of like rgbglow but rgbglow had a lot of annoying parts which made running it kinda meh, this map however features quite a lot of boosters and possible 'spins' so if youre not a big fan of those it might not be your favorite to run at max speed (only rly an issue if ure going for the most optimal run, but i have tweaked the parts multiple times to make it easier and not as frustrating)

If its too much please let me know for my next map so i know what to change, im always looking to improve at map making (funny how i say this yet i keep making glow maps xd, maybe one day ill make something more creative)

Map pro_bhopper fixed

Auto maps are being made incorrectly in regards to what most players insist is one of the main aspects of auto gameplay: Finding and perfecting a route.

This map was made to prove my point.

Before all the bitter auto rands take a moment between posting irrational arguments on sourcejump TAS videos to comment here and put me on blast for 'hating on auto', understand that I am not hating on auto, I'm providing help to make auto maps more popular and competitive.

The problem with how most auto maps are being made, is the distance between the blocks are too far apart to allow for much variation in the route. The map itself pretty much dictates the route and doesn't allow the player much room to find faster ways around the map, resulting in banal, braindead gameplay. Maps like this aren't very competitive and result in most of the top times being very similar. bhop_muchfast is a good example of this.

Creating maps with more route options by adding more bhop blocks with less space between them will make your map more popular and competitive by allowing newer players to experience them, seasoned players to speedrun them, and normal / scroll players to play them. The top times will have much more variety and every run of the map will be different. bhop_cw_journey, for example.
